post_text:
Please see the link below for information regarding the GMC COVID-19 Protocols for fall sporting events.

https://twitter.com/pilotsprincipal/status/1297160626431766530?s=20

We understand that the protocols may not be what we all want. However, we ask that you please keep in mind that these are the protocols that we must abide by in order to operate within the order from the Ohio Department of Health and Gov. DeWine. The protocols listed below allow our student-athletes to have a season, to compete amongst areas schools, to learn the life-long lessons that assist in the physical, emotional, and social development of our students. We ask that you please follow these protocols with the understanding that this is what we must do in order to ensure our student-athletes can play.

Thank you Pilot Nation!!

Ayersville Elementary P.T.O.
May 4 at 2:45 PM ·

IT'S TEACHER APPRECIATION WEEK! 🍎

There aren't enough thank yous or gifts in the world to be enough, but we wanted to present this token of appreciation. Teachers often read books to their students, so we thought we'd "read" a book to them. 😊 It's called "Because I Had a Teacher" written by Kobi Yamada and illustrated by Natalie Russell.

Thank you to everyone who participated in this special video for our teachers and staff! Thank you, educators, for everything you give of yourselves to Pilot Nation.

To find this book and more, visit www.live-inspired.com or Compendium on Facebook. #compendiumliveinspired #pilotpride #pilotnation #gopilots #thankyouteachers #teacherappreciationweek #ayersvilleelementarypto

post_text:
The past couple of days, Mr. Sheridan and I have been calling the high school students to resolve their connection issues. Unfortunately their has not been a '1 Fix for All'. Many students are now connected but I know many of you are not.

I feel that the most efficient way for us to handle the remaining concerns is to be able to work on the devices directly.

I am asking that if you are having issues connecting to websites, please write down your login and password information on a piece of paper and place it in your laptop.

Next please bring your laptop to the school using the car rider line.

I will be available in the car rider line this evening from 4PM-6PM.

I will also be available in the car rider line tomorrow morning from 9AM-11AM.

We will work on fixing the issue and schedule a return time as soon as possible. Thank you for your patience during this time.

The high school yearbook staff needs your help! We have a yearbook to finish and are determined to make it a memorable one! This will truly be one of our most unique books ever.

Computer Browser issue:
If you see the 'Your connection is not Private' screen or you are having trouble accessing websites, please complete the following steps.

1. Click the 3 Vertical dots in the upper right corner of the browser window

2. Select 'More Tools'

3. Select 'Clear Browsing Data'

4. The drop down at the top should be set to 'All Time'

5. Click the 'Clear Data' button (this will take 2-10 seconds)

6. Click the Advanced button

7. Click the link that says 'proceed to ayersvillels ....'

8. This should bring you to the filter login page.

9. (IF ON A CHROMEBOOK)Click the 'Ayersville Pilots' or 'Chromebook LS SSO' link under the Username and Password boxes

9.1 (IF ON A MacBook) Enter your Username and Password for you laptop in the username and password boxes. Click 'Authenticate'

10.You should now be able to access websites and Google Classroom

A more detailed instruction sheet will be coming soon as well as information regarding tech support during this time away from the school building.

post_text:
During the week of February 10-15 the High School celebrated its 2020 Winter Homecoming Week.

Our spirit days included:
PJ Day - students wore their pajamas to school
Jersey Day - students wore a jersey of their favorite sports teams
America Day - students dressed in patriotic/America flag themes
Tourist Day - students dressed as a tourist that may be traveling
Class Color Day - each class was assigned a color to wear

All of this culminated in a fantastic Homecoming ceremony. Congratulations to all on our court and especially our Queen, Taylor Addington and King, Isaac Schindler!

post_text: Freshman, Luke Schroeder, participated in the Regional Science and Engineering Fair at Northwest Community College this past Saturday. He earned a superior rating and 2nd place in the Environmental category with his project “What is the Best Cover Crop to Prevent Soil Erosion?” Luke also earned the Genius Award and was invited to compete at the Rochester, New York Environmental Science Fair. Luke was also awarded the Lee Family Creativity Award. In the high school division, Luke placed 3rd overall, earning the Paul Oberhausen award. This allows Luke to be invited to the International Science Fair in Anaheim, California, to be an observer. Way to go, Luke!
